## OWASP Top 10 Enforcement

### A01: Broken Access Control — CRITICAL
- Authorization middleware on EVERY route handling sensitive data
- Resource-level checks (not just route-level): admin can delete anyone, users delete themselves only
- Never expose internal IDs or use sequential/predictable identifiers

### A02: Cryptographic Failures — CRITICAL
- AES-256-GCM for data at rest, TLS 1.3 for data in transit
- NEVER use MD5, SHA1, DES, RC4
- bcrypt with cost factor 12+ for passwords
- Keys in secret manager (Vault/KMS), never in source code, rotate annually

### A03: Injection — CRITICAL
- Parameterized queries or ORM exclusively — NEVER string concatenation in SQL
- `execFile()` instead of `exec()` for shell commands
- Sanitize all inputs before rendering (DOMPurify if innerHTML required)
- Never use `eval()`, `new Function()`, `setTimeout(string)`, `document.write()`

### A04: Insecure Design — HIGH
- Threat model for every new feature
- Rate limiting, input validation, error handling on every endpoint
- Never expose stack traces or internal errors in production responses

### A05: Security Misconfiguration — HIGH
- Helmet.js with strict CSP configuration on every Express/Koa/Fastify app
- Debug mode OFF in production
- Default credentials changed on all services
- Security headers: CSP, X-Frame-Options: DENY, X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff, HSTS (1yr+), Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

### A06: Vulnerable Components — HIGH
- `npm audit` after every install — block Critical/High CVEs
- Dependabot/Renovate for automated updates
- License compliance: MIT/Apache/BSD approved; GPL/AGPL/SSPL prohibited

### A07: Authentication Failures — CRITICAL
- OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect with established libraries
- Short-lived access tokens (15min) + longer refresh tokens (7d) in HTTP-only, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies
- NEVER store tokens in localStorage
- MFA for critical operations
- Password policy: min 12 chars, uppercase, lowercase, number, special char

### A08: Data Integrity Failures — HIGH
- Sign release artifacts with GPG
- `npm ci` in CI (never `npm install`)
- Verify package integrity with `npm verify`
- Never deserialize untrusted data with code-executing revivers

### A09: Security Logging Failures — MEDIUM
- Log all auth events (login, logout, failure) with userId, IP, user-agent, timestamp
- Log all authorization failures with resource, action, reason
- NEVER log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, credit cards, SSNs, PII)
- Structured JSON logging format

### A10: SSRF — CRITICAL
- Validate ALL user-supplied URLs: protocol (HTTPS only), hostname allowlist, block private networks (localhost, 192.168.x, 10.x)
- Never fetch arbitrary URLs from user input without validation

